us accounting problems. They were discontinued with the dissolution of the Committee in 1959 under a recommendation from the Special Committee on Research Program.<ref>{{cite journal |url= http://umiss.lib.olemiss.edu:82/articles/1032933.3732/1.PDF |author= Zeff, Stephen A. |title= The work of the special committee on research program |accessdate= 10 October 2016 |work= Accounting Historians Journal |publisher= [[Academy of Accounting Historians]] |date= December 2001 |volume= 28 |issue= 2 |pages= 141\u2013186 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> In all, 17 [[wikt:bulletin|bulletins]] were issued; however, the lack of [[binding authority]] over [[AICPA]]'s membership reduced the influence of, and compliance with the content of the bulletins. The Accounting Research Bulletins have all been superseded by the [[Accounting Standards Codification]] (ASC).\n\nWith the permission of the AICPA, the full text of Accounting Research Bulletins has been posted on the website of the [[John Davis Williams|J.D. Williams]] [[Library]] of the University of Mississippi.\n\n==List of Accounting Research Bulletins==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" \n! width=\"100\"|No. !! width=\"600\"|Official title !! width=\"150\"|Issued on \n|-\n|align=\"center\" |1||General Introduction and Rules Formerly Adopted [https://egrove.olemiss.edu/dl_aia/295 full-text]||align=\"center\" |1939 September  \n|-\n|align=\"center\" |2||Unamortized Discount and Redemption Premium on Bonds Refunded [https://egrove.olemiss.edu/dl_aia/308]||align=\"center\" |1939 September  \n|-\n|align=\"center\" |3||Quasi-Reorganization or Corporate Readjustment\u2014Amplification of Institute Rule No. 2 of 1934 [https://egrove.olemiss.edu/dl_aia/320]||align=\"center\" |1939 September \n|-\n|align=\"center\" |4||Foreign Operations and Foreign Exchange [https://egrove.olemiss.edu/dl_aia/332]||align=\"center\" |1939 December \n|-\n|align=\"center\" |5||Depr